'''情色性'''（{{lang-en|Eroticism}}）<ref>{{cite book|title=情色朝鮮：那些被迫忍受、壓抑的韓國近代性慾實錄|url=https://books.google.com.hk/books?id=4rzvDwAAQBAJ&pg=PT3|author=朴永圭|publisher=創意市集|date=2020-06-22|accessdate=2020-12-27|isbn=9789579199902}}</ref>是指引起[[人类的性|性]]感受的特质<ref name=merriam>{{cite web|title=Eroticism|url=http://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/eroticism|work=Merriam-Webster|accessdate=2011-08-07|archive-date=2020-08-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200805031405/https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/eroticism|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=eroticism|url=https://dictionary.cambridge.org/dictionary/english-chinese-traditional/eroticism?q=Eroticism|work=Cambridge Dictionary|accessdate=2020-12-26}}</ref>，以及关于[[性欲|性欲]]、[[感官|感官]]、[[浪漫關係|浪漫關係]]的[[美学|美学]]思辨。此一特質能夠在不同的藝術作品上找到，比如[[绘画|绘画]]、[[雕塑|雕塑]]、[[魅力摄影|照片]]、[[戏剧|戏剧]]、[[床戏|電影]]、[[音乐|音乐]]、[[情色文學|文學]]、廣告。

正如法國小說家[[奥诺雷·德·巴尔扎克|奥诺雷·德·巴尔扎克]]指出，情色性的定義不僅只與某人的[[性倫理|性道德]]有關，還取決於其所身處的文化和時代<ref>Balzac, "The Physiology of Marriage" (1826), trans. Sharon Marcus (1997), Aphorism XXVI, 65</ref><ref>Grande, L., "Laws and Attitudes towards Homosexuality from Antiquity to the Modern Era", Ponte 43:4-5 (1987), pp. 122-129</ref><ref>Gauthier, Albert, "La sodomie dans le droit canonique medieval" in L'Erotisme au Moyen Age: Etudes presentees au IIe Colloque de l'Institut d'Etudes Medievales, 3-4 Avril 1976, ed. Roy, Bruno (Montreal: Ed. Aurore, 1977), pp. 109-122</ref>。

==定義==
有鑑於情色的本質是流動的<ref>Evans, David T., Sexual Citizenship: The Material Construction of Sexualities, (New York: Routledge, 1993)</ref>，故早期定義將它設想成某種形式的肉體或浪漫之愛，有的則直接將其等同性慾。比如1755年版的《[[百科全书，或科学、艺术和工艺详解词典|百科全书，或科学、艺术和工艺详解词典]]》將情色定義為「一個形容词，其适用于一切跟两性之爱有关的事物；它特指那種無節制的放蕩」<ref>''Encyclopédie'' (1755), quoted in Lynn Hunt ed., ''Eroticism and the Body Politic'' (London 1991) p. 90</ref>、 

情色的定義完全取決於觀者的文化和品味<ref>Foster. Jeannette H., Sex Variant Women in Literature: A Historical and Quantitative Survey 2nd ed., (New York: Vantage Press, 1956) (repr. Baltimore: Diana Press, 1975)</ref><ref>Weinberg, M., & A. Bell, Homosexuality: An Annotated Bibliography, (New York: 1972)</ref>，故此人們乃至批判者很容易將完全依賴上述判斷的情色性跟[[色情|色情]]混淆<ref>{{cite book|title=Debating Pornography|last1=Altman|first1=A.|last2=Watson|first2=L.|isbn=978-0-19-935871-7|page=64|publisher=Oxford University Press|year=2019}}</ref>。反色情活動家[[安德里亞·德沃金|安德里亞·德沃金]]表示：「情色只不過是更高檔次的色情罷了；它們有着更好的制作、更好的构思、更好的执行過程、更好的包装，為較上流之人士而設計」<ref>{{cite book |title=Pornography: Men Possessing Women |last=Dworkin |first=Andrea |year=1981 |isbn=978-0-399-12619-2 |pages=39}}</ref>。[[林恩·亨特|林恩·亨特]]就這類型的混淆寫道：「這证明了……很難清楚劃分情色與色情……情色與色情分離的歷史乃待人補白」<ref>Hunt, "Introduction", in Hunt ed., ''Eroticism'' p. 4</ref>。

== 生物演化 ==
情色性与文化及其色情製品有关，演化心理学已揭示了情色性如何影響人性的演化<ref>{{Cite book|title=The Mating Mind: How Sexual Choice Shaped the Evolution of Human Nature|last=Miller|first=Geoffrey|publisher=Vintage|year=2001|location=London}}</ref>。

==精神分析学==
[[File:Godward_The_Old_Old_Story_1903.jpg|thumb]]的《很久很久以前的故事》（The Old, Old Story）]]
[[精神分析学|心理治療師]]在[[西格蒙德·弗洛伊德|西格蒙德·弗洛伊德]]的影響之下<ref>Dollimore, Jonathan, Sexual Dissidence: Augusutine to Wilde, Freud to Foucault (Oxford: Clarendon, 1991), 105-8. Clarendon Press, 1991. {{ISBN|9780198112693}}</ref>，開始經由希臘哲學了解情色背後的[[美学|審美]]<ref>Hunt, "Introduction", in Hunt ed., Eroticism p. 13</ref>。對於[[柏拉图|柏拉图]]而言，当主体寻求超越自身，与客体/他者交融时，[[厄洛斯|厄洛斯]]就会有一种近乎超然的表现：「一條正確的途徑……可以自己遵循着它去愛，先從這個個別的美的東西開始……到一切美的形體，更從美的形體到那些美的行動，從美的行動到美的知識，最後從各種知識終於到達那種無關是關於美的知識」<ref>''The Symposium'', in Benjamin Jowett trans., ''The Essential Plato'' (1871/1999), 746. However, note that Jowett's Victorian-era translation has asserted a reading of Plato that tends toward the physical-sex-less (e.g. the current sense of a ''platonic'' relationship), compared to later scholars from Walter Pater through Michel Foucault, to the present. See Adam Lee, ''The Platonism of Walter Pater: Embodied Equity'' (Oxford University Press, 2020). {{ISBN|9780192588135}}; and, again, Dollimore (1991).</ref>。

==法國哲學==
當代法國對於情色性的概念可追溯至[[啟蒙時代|啟蒙時代]]<ref>Coward, D.A., "Attitudes to Homosexuality in Eighteenth Century France", Journal of European Studies 10, pp. 236 ff.</ref>，「在18世紀期間，字典将情色定义为跟愛有關的事物……情色性是私人事務對於公共領域的入侵」<ref>Hunt, "Introduction", in Hunt ed., ''Eroticism'' p. 3 and p. 5</ref>。法国哲学家[[喬治·巴代伊|喬治·巴代伊]]於20世紀間發表了同樣的觀點，他認為情色性消去了人的主體性與人性之間的界限——暫時地消去理性的世界<ref>L'érotisme, by Georges Bataille, Paris (1957: UK publication 1962) {{ISBN|978-2-7073-0253-3}}</ref>，並指「情色性當中的慾望是战胜禁忌的慾望。它以人与自身的冲突为前提」<ref>George Bataille, ''Eroticism'' (Penguin 2001) p. 256</ref>。對於巴代伊等一眾法國哲學家而言，「情色性並不只關乎性行為，它是一種心理上的追求……情色性即是對於生與死的認同」<ref>Bataille, ''Eroticism'' p. 11</ref>。

==非異性戀==
[[File:Ciągliński_Symbolic_dance.jpg|thumb]]
[[酷儿理论|酷儿理论]]和[[酷儿研究|LGBT研究]]會從[[非異性戀|非異性戀]]的角度探討情色性，並認為現代主義和精神分析對於情色性的看法十分古板<ref>Morton, Donald, ed., The Material Queer: A LesBiGay Cultural Studies Reader, (Boulder CO: Westview, 1996)</ref> 、[[异性恋主义|以異性戀為中心]]<ref>Cohen, Ed, Talk on the Wilde Side: Towards a Genealogy of a Discourse on Male Sexualities, (New York: Routledge, 1999)</ref>，表示有關論述主要由「誤認為自己的壓抑性偏好」是常态的「少数精英、异性戀、资产阶级男性」撰写，受眾同是這一批人<ref>Flannigan-Saint-Aubin, Arthur. "'Black Gay Male' Discourse: Reading Race and Sexuality Between the Lines". Journal of the History of Sexuality 3:3 (1993): 468-90.</ref><ref>Aries, Philippe & Andre Bejin, eds., Western Sexuality: Practice and Precept in Past and Present, (Oxford: Blackwell, 1985; orig. pub. as Sexualities Occidentales, Paris: Editions du Seuil/Communications, 1982)</ref><ref>Bullough, Vern L., "Homosexuality and the Medical Model", Journal of Homosexuality 1:6 (1975), pp. 99-110</ref>。

{{link-en|伊芙·科索夫斯基·塞奇威克|Eve Kosofsky Sedgwick}}<ref>from Abelove, Henry, Michele Aina Barale, and David Halperin, eds., The Lesbian and Gay Studies Reader, (New York: Routledge: 1993) Eve Kosofsky Sedgewick: Epistemology of the closet, 45</ref>、[[蓋兒·魯賓|蓋兒·魯賓]]<ref>from Abelove, Henry, Michele Aina Barale, and David Halperin, eds., The Lesbian and Gay Studies Reader, (New York: Routledge: 1993) Gayle S. Rubin: Notes for a radical theory of the politics of sexuality, 3</ref>、{{link-en|玛丽莲·弗莱|Marilyn Frye}}等一眾理論家<ref>from Abelove, Henry, Michele Aina Barale, and David Halperin, eds., The Lesbian and Gay Studies Reader, (New York: Routledge: 1993) Marilyn Frye: Some reflections on separatism and power, 91</ref>分别从异性恋、[[女同性恋|女同性恋]]、[[分离主义|分离主义]]的角度，去為情色性進行大量論述，他們認為情色性既是一种政治力量<ref>Marshall, John, "Pansies, Perverts and Macho Men: Changing Conceptions of Male Homosexuality", in Kenneth Plummer, ed., The Making of the Modern Homosexual, (London: Hutchinson, 1981), 133-54</ref>，也是对於边缘化群体的文化批判<ref>Fone, Byrne R.S., "Some Notes Toward a History of Gay People", The Advocate no. 259 (Jan 25, 1979), pp. 17-19 & no. 260 (Feb 28, 1979), pp. 11-13</ref>。[[马里奥·巴尔加斯·略萨|马里奥·巴尔加斯·略萨]]總結道：「情色性有其自身的道德正當性。因为它说快乐对我来说就足够了；它是個體主權的表現」<ref>Mangan, J. A. "Men, Masculinity, and Sexuality: Some Recent Literature". Journal of the History of Sexuality 3:2 (1992): 303-13</ref>。

